ed the Earth,\" which; without qualification or exception is the best story of its. kind I have ever read. Mere power to you. Keep up the good work and be sure to have the science in the stories correct so that I shall not be obliged to put the ban on them as I was obliged to do with the Muehlbach \"historical\" novels in which the history in so many cases never happened. \r\n\r\nBRADFORD BUTLER, Counselor at Law, New York, N. Y. \r\n\r\n[Here is a man of learning, an attorney at law, who upholds our view that classics, like Jules Verne and H. G. Wells, should be reprinted in a magazine of the type of AMAZING STORIES. A few readers have written us that we should not print Jules Verne, because his works are available in every library. Nevertheless we believe that the vast majority of our readers, along with Mr. Butler, do not feel like running to the library, where it is not always possible to secure the book. Also, many of our readers no doubt want to reread their favorite author in AMAZING STORIES now, just as, we are sure, many new stories which we print in AMAZING STORIES today will be reread by the younger generation in years to come.â€”EDITOR.]  '),(952,'Item',1819,1,'23_010001','23_010001 Highty Tighties Virginia Tech Highty Tighties sweater patch Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets Museum Case 18 Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets patch approx 6\" x 7\" '),(953,'Item',1820,1,'23_010002','23_010002 Highty Tighties Highty Tighties inside Lane Stadium Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets Museum Case 18 Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets photograph approx 10\" x 8\" '),(954,'Item',1821,1,'23_010003','23_010003 Highty Tighties Highty Tighties pay final tribute to fan (Roanoke Times) Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets Museum Case 18 Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets clipping (information artifact) approx 6\" x 8\" '),(955,'Item',1822,1,'23_010004','23_010004 Highty Tighties 1973 Highty Tighties Drill Team Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets Museum Case 18 Virginia Tech Corps of Cadets photograph approx